<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="30.[151,1435,1976,2036]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,255,1976,2000]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Note</emphasis>
. At a first look the general pattern on the fore wing could be mistaken with those of 
<taxonomicName box="[1220,1350,1976,2000]" class="Insecta" family="Cercopidae" genus="Amberana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elongata">
<emphasis box="[1220,1350,1976,2000]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">A. elongata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but the spots of colour are clearer and bigger for 
<taxonomicName box="[614,726,2012,2036]" class="Insecta" family="Cercopidae" genus="Amberana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pascali">
<emphasis box="[614,726,2012,2036]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">A. pascali</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,1042,151,176]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1436,151,319]" box="[199,1042,151,176]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,326,152,176]" pageId="31" pageNumber="32">Etymology</emphasis>
. Named after Pascal, the first name of the first author’s brother.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
